{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:psalms.9",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 9,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 9 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:1",
      "text": "For the end, a Psalm of David, concerning the secrets of the Son. - I will give thanks to thee, O Lord, with my whole heart; I will recount all thy wonderful works.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:2",
      "text": "I will be glad and exult in thee: I will sing to thy name, O thou Most High.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:3",
      "text": "When mine enemies are turned back, they shall be feeble and perish at thy presence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:4",
      "text": "For thou hast maintained my cause and my right; thou satest on the throne, that judgest righteousness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:5",
      "text": "Thou hast rebuked the nations, and the ungodly one has perished; thou hast blotted out their name for ever, even for ever and ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:6",
      "text": "The swords of the enemy have failed utterly; and thou hast destroyed cities: their memorial has been destroyed with a noise,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:7",
      "text": "but the Lord endures for ever: he has prepared his throne for judgement.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:8",
      "text": "And he will judge the world in righteousness, he will judge the nations in uprightness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:9",
      "text": "The Lord also is become a refuge for the poor, a seasonable help, in affliction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:10",
      "text": "And let them that know thy name hope in thee: for thou, O Lord, hast not failed them that diligently seek thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:11",
      "text": "Sing praises to the Lord, who dwells in Sion: declare his dealings among the nations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:12",
      "text": "For he remembered them, in making inquisition for blood: he has not forgotten the supplication of the poor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:13",
      "text": "Have mercy upon me, O Lord; look upon my affliction which I suffer of mine enemies, thou that liftest me up from the gates of death:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:14",
      "text": "that I may declare all thy praises in the gates of the daughter of Sion: I will exult in thy salvation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:15",
      "text": "The heathen are caught in the destruction which they planned: in the very snare which they hid is their foot taken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:16",
      "text": "The Lord is known as executing judgements: the sinner is taken in the works of his hands. A song of Pause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:17",
      "text": "Let sinners be driven away into Hades, even all the nations that forget God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:18",
      "text": "For the poor shall not be forgotten for ever: the patience of the needy ones shall not perish for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:19",
      "text": "Arise, O Lord, let not man prevail: let the heathen be judged before thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.9.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 9:20",
      "text": "Appoint, O Lord, a lawgiver over them: let the heathen know that they are men. Pause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
